snippet.textDisplay:
Dr Mike
I have a very hard question because I have asked over 50 doctors with no answer so maybe you can help.

“What is wrong with me and how can we stop the pain/ symptoms/ spasms/ seizures/ fatigue/ fever/ etc.”

I was an emergency c-section baby in fetal distress born 2 months earlier yet only developed as of 3 months premature. I have a very rare Partial chromosome deletion that kills most babies in the womb, which is why I’m so rare to be 28 with my condition.

But none of that explains my issues/ symptoms. I have been unable to work for almost a year now because it’s gotten so bad that I’m into much pain and I need supervision. As of last summer I was no longer even allowed to live on my own in case I have a medical issue and so 28th I had to move back in with my parents. My entire life we have been seeing doctor after doctor and specialists after specialist. And have been turned away by many doctors, Because they don’t know how to help me but no there’s something wrong but there’s nothing else they can do. This happened again last Monday. I am getting desperate. And I need a doctor to help me. But right now All they can do is give me meds To help the symptoms not the issue. I have to be taking Oxy Multiple times a day for two years. And multiple Strong muscle relaxers multiple times a day for over two years probably over three. I eat one meal a day to meals if I can manage due to all the pain and nausea. I know you’re not the Doctor Who can help me But I’m putting it out there because I’m desperate just tired of being sick and tired of being a burden and I’m tired of going to doctors appointments and therapy every week multiple times a week. I need help and I don’t want to continue taking all of these medications. I am taking large amounts of opioids and I’m not addicted but I’ve seen what it is done to people in my family and my uncle was killed by the police because of those addictions. I don’t want to be another person in the opioid crisis But I don’t want to be in pain either. I don’t want to sit at home playing video games and watching YouTube all day. I want to work I want to life I want to be able to take my service dog on a daily walk or to the park, Instead of paying my little sister to. I need help from the doctor. I need answers And I am desperate for those answers and I’m sick and tired of being turned away from doctors because they can’t help me. Please help me please.

snippet.textDisplay:
Hey Doctor Mike, not an Anti-Vax here but what could cause a vaccine to not work on someone?
I recently found through a random checkup that I've got Hepatitis B, I've got all my vaccines for it since being a child ( coming from a tropical country) and all the boosters on time... The first test came up positive for Hepatitis B, the doctor told me I was contagious... We ran a second test and found out I actually developed a immunity after being exposed to Hepatitis B yet still positive for the virus, it also showed my liver is doing perfectly fine as well! So the doctor was hella confused looking at me like "what are you?", the biologist was hella confused, I'm hella confused... The doctor told me to run tests every year or so to see if that changes over time... What do you think is going on with me Dr Mike? How can I be immune, not sick, yet contagious?

snippet.textDisplay:
For the flu thing, the biggest misconception of evolution is it doesn't necessarily make an organism better. Like how some animals lose some of their adaptations. Like for example, whales and dolphins had legs. The only part that is still left is a pelvic bone (Which they use for mating now, but you get the idea) I blame pokemon for people thinking this is how evolution works lol


How vaccines work is they use either a weakened version of a virus or bacteria.(sometimes they are just dead bacteria or viruses as well. Which is why people with no immune system can still get a vaccine without issues) You're immune system fights the virus or bacteria and two cells stay around to provide "memory" of what killed the infection. These are celled memory B cells and T cells. So, if the flu changes too much these cells will not identify these as the flu.

snippet.textDisplay: In regards to the drinking during eating question: as someone who is going through the process of preparing for bariatric surgery, not drinking during meals is one of the biggest habits we work on before surgery.  Not drinking allows food to stay in your stomach longer, helping you feel fuller sooner, and for longer periods after the meal is over.  It also helps food to break down more completely before moving along to the intestines.  I've found it one of the bigger pieces to losing weight during this process, and my husband tried it out and found he stopped eating sooner during meals and felt satisfied for longer afterwards.  I LOVE drinking during meals and its a very hard habit to change, but it has made demonstrable difference.  The key is to not drink during and for up to half an hour after.
